<paragraph blockId="8.[144,759,659,926]" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis box="[144,262,660,681]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Distinguished from all congeners, except 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Costa, Lacerda &amp; Tanizaki" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[144,316,690,711]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Leptolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="155" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="citrinipinnis">
<emphasis box="[144,316,690,711]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">L. citrinipinnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in having dorsal-fin origin in vertical between base of seventh and ninth anal-fin rays (vs. between base of second and sixth anal-fin rays). It differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Costa, Lacerda &amp; Tanizaki" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[326,498,782,803]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Leptolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="155" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="citrinipinnis">
<emphasis box="[326,498,782,803]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">L. citrinipinnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having caudal fin lanceolate (vs. elliptical), dark-red stripe on distal margin of dorsal and anal fins, and dorsal and ventral margin of caudal fin in males (vs. reddish brown pigmentation diffuse).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[144,730,966,988]" box="[144,730,966,988]" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis box="[144,251,966,987]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">Remarks:</emphasis>
